CAPE TOWN - It's Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula's turn to deliver his department's budget vote on Friday. He's expected to outline steps to try professionalise the taxi industry. It's been a prominent focus for the minister who said the sector had tremendous potential to become a model for real empowerment. The industry generates R40 billion each year. Mbalula's spokesperson Ayanda-Allie Paine said: “The minister will also share plans on massive road infrastructure projects that form part of government’s economic recovery plan.” Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.